review_title: Great Fit But Will Eventually "Wear" Down
reviews:
I, purchased Hanes Undershirts in the past, simply to see what other type of Men's Undershirts were on the market. I, frequently would always purchase Fruit of the Loom, but would change, whenever there was a sale on any of these two brands. What I will say, both Men's Undershirts from both brands are very similar in their quality, fit and style. Over time, these Undershirts will fade in colour, shrink, and the material to begin to unravel. The amount of times, I had to rip loose threading, was more than what I would consider normal.

Again, I've worn Men's Undershirts, for more than 20 years and the quality has definitely changed. These shirts and much more thinner in fabric, compared to what I originally remember. The life span is relatively shorter after several washes, whereby you will notice that the texture and fabric will no longer hold together and the colour will begin to fade.

These are good if you want to wear something, just for relaxing or working around the house. However, for everyday wear, you will probably have to replace and purchase a new set within 6 to 8 weeks. This will become an expensive activity to consistently having to replace and re-order these.

I, still have faith that somewhere down the road, Hanes will improve their quality because they are a reputable brand; they just need to put value back into their products.
product_name: Hanes Men's Tagless¬Æ ComfortSoft¬Æ White Undershirt 6-Pack

reviews: This is the worst product I‚Äôve ever bought online. The fabric is thin and scratchy, the seams have way too much extra thread hanging off the ends (and if you cut it the seams start undoing), AND it started shedding little white fibres EVERYWHERE as soon as I opened the package. These are the WORST and I don‚Äôt understand how anyone has received this positively. I‚Äôm expecting a refund because this is absolutel not at all what was advertised.
product_name: Hanes Men's Tagless¬Æ ComfortSoft¬Æ White Undershirt 6-Pack

reviews:
These fit as expected and are very comfortable. I have purchased black and grey versions of these before, but never white. While they are made of the exact same material and appear to be of the same quality, they appear to be slightly see through/transparent while wearing them, especially if they fit you tight. Seems to be a common and unfortunate corollary of white fabrics.

Pros:
- Extremely comfortable;
- No tags to itch you;
- Bottom is hemmed!!! That's a big deal to me. Some other brands that I have are not and they fray at the bottom over time. Also gives it a finished look.

Cons:
- Slightly transparent, becomes more evident the tighter it fits

Would definitely buy again. 1 star deducted for the slight transparency in fabric issue.
product_name: Hanes Men's Tagless¬Æ ComfortSoft¬Æ White Undershirt 6-Pack

reviews: I finally received this hat after having ordered it a month ago. There is a mistake in this add that has led to me receiving a colour that I did not want. Under the colour options when ordering, the white and beige options show the same white hat picture. When I opened the packaging, I was disappointed to see that the hat I received was a light brown instead of the white/cream I thought I was receiving. Also, the add states that it fits size 0-36 months. My daughter has just turned one and is on the small size. This hat barely fits her head. I feel like I would need to stretch it before she wears it. Overall I am very dissatisfied which is unfortunate as I was looking forward to this cute hat.

reviews:

When I initially ordered this item I was sent a wrong color. The picture of beige is more like white here but it is more like brown. However the seller was amazing in no time they fixed the issue.
The hat did look big when I saw it. But now that I have my baby girl she is 7.5ilbs and it fits her. Her head circumference is 14cm and I think she will wear it all winter. It doesn't slide off like most other hand knitted ones.
My only thing is the height of it is too big . But I guess she will just grow into it for now it gives like a cone shape look. Which is still good.

reviews: Gloves are insanely stylish, you can wear them with anything and I have gotten so many compliments on them. One thing I love about this pair of gloves is no brand logos and inner brownish color. The only thing I don't like about the gloves is that they don't keep you that warm. When I bought them, I saw on the ad that they are good until -20 degrees Celsius, but I find at even -10 you are feeling cold. They are good for cold days, but not great for Canadian snow snowstorms where the temperature drops to below -30, especially in Montreal.
product_name: Touchscreen Leather Gloves for Men's Texting Driving Winter Christmas

review_title: Too thin and not warm enough
reviews:
Very thin glove. Expected the leather and the fur to be a bit thicker. Tighter on the palm, but fits. I do expect the to leather to expand. Definetly not meant for -20 degrees c or -4 Fahrenheit. Meant for -5 degrees c or
23 Fahrenheit.
I am worried that it won‚Äôt last.
product_name: Touchscreen Leather Gloves for Men's Texting Driving Winter Christmas

reviews:
Just received this product. It was received faster than expected. The product is as described and meets my expectations.
Feels and look like quality gloves. Bought medium in accordance with the fitting chart and the gloves fit me perfectly, just like a glove.
Contrary to the product name, the interior lining is not cashmere. As shown in the product photos, the lining is made of synthetic plush, quality of which clashes with the leather.
Time will tell if these will last. In any case these are good value for the price.
Recommended!
product_name: Touchscreen Leather Gloves for Men's Texting Driving Winter Christmas

reviews: I'm giving this purchase a two simply for the fact if false advertising. They are beautiful gloves, and they fit perfectly. As pleasing as they might be aesthetically, it doesn't compensate for the fact your hands, even in 3 degree weather, are very very cold. And these gloves are meant to withstand -20 degrees. If your looking for style but lack of warmth I would go through with a purchase otherwise save your money and go get a pair of thermal gloves.
product_name: Touchscreen Leather Gloves for Men's Texting Driving Winter Christmas

review_title: Ok at best. Not as warm as advertised
reviews:
Expected better and warmer. They are ok down to a very maximum of 14F (-10C). Leather is nice and they are comfy. Beware of size as they are made with long fingers. I usually fit in XL for width and settle with L for finger length. I have a 1/3 inch loose at the tip making it hard to use my phone or even car controls. Could have exchanged them (I know) but they were tighter in the 1st week and the box was mistakenly used has a drawing board by my kid. Good for the price but I don‚Äôt think I‚Äôll repeat.

I buy leather gloves yearly and it is the model that stretched the most after a week‚Äôs usage
product_name: Touchscreen Leather Gloves for Men's Texting Driving Winter Christmas

reviews:
I feel pretty oh so pretty!
While I do believe the entire surface of the glove works with my phone screen I've found it only works well with just the tip of my finger/glove.
Definitely warm. Tried them on inside and my hands were sweating within a minute.
Perfect for event days and cold evening raids in pokemon go. GO TEAM VALOR! :-D
product_name: Touchscreen Leather Gloves for Men's Texting Driving Winter Christmas

reviews:
Waited a few months before posting review. The gloves were a bit stiff and Ill fitting when recieved but having worn leather before I new I had to brake them in.

I use them daily and they still look brand new. No scuffs or tears and they now fit well and feel like second skin.

Would recommend these to anyone.

review_title: Pricewise it‚Äôs pretty good, not so sure about the leather though‚Ä¶
reviews:
Initially, I bought a small pair of brown leather gloves from the seller for retail price which was $40. A day later it drops down to $23 for a black pair which I also purchased.

Having a pair and both black and brown, I can honestly say save your money. The brown pair what is a gift to a friend From the looks of it, it‚Äôs leather - when you put it on and smell the glove, it seems synthetic which it probably is. When it comes to warmth, don‚Äôt expect your hands to feel as warm and -5 degree weather. The only positive with this is that the touchscreen function actually works.

Overall, this glove looks nice and performs well when using your phone. That‚Äôs it.

reviews: When I initially bought these gloves, the size didn't fit true to size but were fine. The touchscreen portion only works for the very finger tips which were annoying but not as bad. product_name: Touchscreen Leather Gloves for Men's Texting Driving Winter Christmas

review_title: Inner liner is extremely prone to generatic static electricity.

product_name: Touchscreen Leather Gloves for Men's Texting Driving Winter Christmas

review_title: High quality, but not very warm
reviews:
Like almost every other review says, they look good, they feel good, they are comfortable and fit well, but they are not as warm as they claim. In -20 degrees your hands will still be cold.

I wouldn't buy them to use as winter gloves, but they work great to keep your hands warm on the way driving to work in the winter, or going for a quick walk outside. Being able to use your phone or touchscreen car stereo is also nice.

The leather is good quality, and the insides are very soft and comfortable. For $40 you can't go wrong.
product_name: Touchscreen Leather Gloves for Men's Texting Driving Winter Christmas

review_title: Fits and feels good... sort of?
reviews: I'm a size 9.5-10 foot depending on the type of shoe. These socks fit relatively well and feel good. HOWEVER, after an hour (and more) of use... the elastic starts to constrict around your calves. When you wear them for an entire work day (8 hours) and come home to take them off you'll literally see indentations in your calves cause the elastic is so gosh darn tight for whatever reason. Even several washes in the past several months did nothing to loosen them up.
product_name: Dockers Men's 5-Pack Classics Dress Dobby Crew Socks

review_title: Exactly what I was hoping for.
reviews:
These are good quality dress socks, with a bit of detail to make them stand out from a basic black sock. I like the subtle detail.

Unlike some patterned socks where the threads creating the patterns catch on your toes when you try and put them on, these are properly made and go on smoothly. I find they have a nice weight, and they stay up without being so tight that they cut off my circulation.

I'll be buying them again, and would recommend them for business or casual use. Even my wife steals them.
product_name: Dockers Men's 5-Pack Classics Dress Dobby Crew Socks

reviews: I wear size 11 shoes and I bought "10-13 Sock/6-12 Shoe", yet the heels ride up a couple of inches. Should have selected smaller size. Their size chart is misleading or perhaps I should stay away from these.
product_name: Dockers Men's 5-Pack Classics Dress Dobby Crew Socks

review_title: Way too tight at the top - wearing for more than 1hr is painful
reviews:
Like other reviewers have said, these socks are only good for a short wear, I've literally put these on just to do the laundry and that was still too long/left me with sore calves from the elastic digging in.

I made the mistake of hoping they would stretch instead of demanding a refund, but they look snazzy?
product_name: Dockers Men's 5-Pack Classics Dress Dobby Crew Socks

reviews: I have couple of dockers cargo pants which I've been using for more than half a decade now. Dockers was known for their high quality material and production quality. I don't know what has happened but these socks only lasted a two months before they were ripped by the toes and sole. Very disappointing.

review_title: I am very disappointed with my purchase of the product Arctrix youth overalls ...
reviews:
To whom this may concern,
I am very disappointed with my purchase of the product Arctrix youth overalls snow bib medium sunset orange.
A while back, I asked for a reimbursement after noticing a defect in the sowing around the ankle. I had to pay shipping fees to get reimbursed so I decided to keep the overalls and fix the stitch myself. As the days went by, more stitches came undone in different areas of the overalls. The knee area was so damaged that I had to ask a specialist to fix the sowing and add an extra layer of material so that it doesn‚Äôt happen again. The material he used was black instead of the orange since he didn‚Äôt have any similar color. This costed me 20,70$ and it is very disappointing because I bought the overalls at a high price and thought I had a good quality product but obviously it isn‚Äôt.
I don‚Äôt see why I would have to pay shipping fees to get reimbursed. I find this ridiculous and disrespectful to the consumer. I would appreciate it if someone would contact me for the reimbursement.

Best regards,
Hania Benzine
product_name: Arctix Youth Overalls Snow Bib

review_title: Great quality, great price - Too long!
reviews:
Didn‚Äôt know how to say they fit, because they are very long in the legs, but other than that, the size fits my 5 year old perfectly. Once the length is over his winter boots, it doesn‚Äôt seem like much of an issue, at least not yet. Really do think they could be a little shorter.
With that asize, the quality is amazing for the price! My little guy loves them! We had a very expensive pair before this, and he always complained about being cold or wet, now he plays for hours, sitting, laying, crawling and climbing thru the snow with no issues. Happy mom over here :)
product_name: Arctix Youth Overalls Snow Bib

reviews:
For those, like me, who were wondering about sizing...
My son is 52 inches. I bought him a Medium. So when he wears them i pull the shoulder straps fully tight and, in his sock feet, they go below his ankles and cover most of his feet but i can still see his toes sticking out from the bottom. So they're a bit long but not to the point of looking silly or feeling cumbersome and should hopefully catch a couple winters out of them depending on growth rate.
Cant speak to quality as we've barely used them but they look nice. Im mostly interested in seeing how the knees hold up since they aren't re-enforced.
product_name: Arctix Youth Overalls Snow Bib

reviews: Fast delivery. Product seems durable and able to withstand the wear 'n tear of a teenage boy at a winter scout camp with no signs of damage. My son wore these over his sweats for two days, when it was -10 deg C, and he stayed warm. Purchased youth "large" and this is a good size for a 13/14 yr old male. Would be even better if they had boot zippers and reinforced Knee but those features would probably increase cost.
product_name: Arctix Youth Overalls Snow Bib

review_title: which fits better. I went with a medium for the waist ...
reviews:
my son is 7. size chart said a small should fit him. These bibs were too tight at the top despite having the stretchable material. Had to return and went with a waist hight bib from arctix, which fits better. I went with a medium for the waist hight bibs which are a bit too big, but will work for now.
My son is thin build, so these are quite small.

I fount mountain warehouse bibs on sale for the same price at a local mall, wish I had found those before buying the second pair of Arctix. the MW were much better quality!

reviews: I bought these for my daughter for Christmas. It is now the end of February and she has been wearing them nearly every day. They are nice and warm and have held up very well. She is an average sized 7 year old, I bought size small, and they leave room to grow in the length. review_title: ... some reason it has been hard to find a good fitting, non bulky snow pant for a not ...
reviews:
ADDITION TO MY RATING FROM LAST YEAR: This is the second pair of Arctix youth overalls that we have purchased. Very happy again!

For some reason it has been hard to find a good fitting, non bulky snow pant for a not terribly skinny 5 year old this year. This Artcix snow pant seems perfect so far (only had them for about a week). Best attributes: not bulky like most snow pants, warm, dry and the brilliant gusset on each side allows for movement and flexibility and an additional sweater underneath if needed. Just a little long but when the next growth spurt occurs, we'll be ready.

review_title: Poor fit. Size chart is both hard to find and inaccurate
reviews: We bought these snowpants for our son. According to the size chart (on manufacturer's website) small is supposed to be a General Size 8. Our son typically takes size 6-7 and these still fit very small. First, the size chart should be included in the product description -- customers shouldn't have to dig for it in reviews to find it. Second, the fitting should be more reliable. Disappointing experience overall.
product_name: Arctix Youth Overalls Snow Bib

review_title: As per other reviewers, these fit small and thin and may measure even smaller than size chart
reviews: My son wore out the knees in one season, but my daughter's lasted to be passed on. So durability depends on how rough your kids are on their clothes in general. I'm a repeat buyer because my kids like the less-bulky snow pants and the price is cheap. Both my older kids outgrew the Large last winter. My son, who is skinny and long (but only 5'3") at 13 years old just barely fits the Extra Large. My daughter at 15, who is petite but more curvy being a girl, finds the extra large a bit tight but tolerable. The hip on the snow pants doesn't really measure the 38" that the chart says. I measured it at 37" which explains the snugness for my daughter. I bought these based on the size chart so be warned: they can be even narrower than the chart says! I just put my 10 year old son in the hand-me-down Large and though it is much too long, it fits very comfortably width-wise.
